This implementation could be useful, if you want to notify the assignee of the issue assigned to him, in which he might not be aware of.

The current behavior of lastViewed field will replace the last viewed timestamp and remove the earlier history of access.

*Situation*
We created a new velocity file in templates/email/html/icludes/fields and include it in some of our email templates ("issueclosed.vm" and "issueresolveconfirmed.vm") by using the following line of code:

{code:title=Include "solution.vm" in email template|theme=FadeToGrey|linenumbers=true|language=html/xml|firstline=0001|collapse=true}
#parse("templates/email/html/includes/fields/solution.vm")
{code}

{code:title=Content of solution.vm|theme=FadeToGrey|linenumbers=true|language=html/xml|firstline=0001|collapse=true}
#disable_html_escaping()
#set ($solution=$customFieldManager.getCustomFieldObjectByName("Solution Documentation")) 	
#if ($issue.getCustomFieldValue($solution))
<tr valign="top">
    <td>
        <strong>Solution:</strong>
    </td>
    <td>
        $!{rendererManager.getRenderedContent("atlassian-wiki-renderer", $issue.getCustomFieldValue($solution), $issue.issueRenderContext)}
    </td>
</tr>
#end
{code}

Having an image added in the custom field "Solution Documentation" by using wiki syntax (\!First Screenshot.png\!) works perfect on any mail being sent from i.e. the issue close event. 

{code:title=The <img>-tag rendererd|theme=FadeToGrey|linenumbers=true|language=html/xml|firstline=0001|collapse=true}
<img src="http://jiratest.hlag.com:8080/jira/secure/attachment/136900/136900_First+Screenshot.png" align="absmiddle" border="0" />
{code}

*Bug*
When using the "Flush Mail Queue" Button in the System -> Mail Queue Panel of the Administration interface, the content of the custom field "Solution Documentation" is still being rendered. With the difference, that the src-attribute of the <img>-tag misses the baseurl. The result is the image is not being shown in the mail client.

{code:title=The <img>-tag rendererd|theme=FadeToGrey|linenumbers=true|language=html/xml|firstline=0001|collapse=true}
<img src="/jira/secure/attachment/136900/136900_First+Screenshot.png" align="absmiddle" border="0" />
