When we click on any of the  "Properties" in the workflow Diagram, it opens a new window, which may lead to confusion for users. For example, if an administrator:
# Start editing a workflow;
# Edit something (which will be displayed in a new tab);
# And click to go back to the step;

He will then have two tabs open with different information in them. If he publishes the workflow in any of the tabs and then goes to the other tab, the workflow will still show the 'Publish Draft' button, which will throw an error if clicked on. This was not the behavior in the Workflow Designer in previous versions of JIRA.

h3. Steps to replicate:
# Go to the Workflows administration and choose one by clicking on _Edit_;
# Select the _Diagram_ mode and click on any of the steps. This will open a window with some information regarding that step;
# Now click on "Properties" or "Conditions" or "Validators" or "Post functions", below the _Options_ title. This will open a new browser window.

h3. Expected Behavior:
JIRA would show the chosen option in the same tab.

